# Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in your values.
Never commit `.env.local` to version control.

## Required — Application will not start without these

```
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
```
Your Supabase project URL.
Found at: Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API → Project URL

```
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJ...
```
Your Supabase anonymous (public) key. Safe to expose in the browser.
Found at: Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API → Project API Keys → anon public

## Required for PDF generation (Sprint 9C)

Set via Supabase CLI — not in .env.local (these are Edge Function secrets):

```
BROWSERLESS_TOKEN=your_browserless_api_token
```
Free tier at browserless.io — 1,000 PDF generations/month.
Set with: `supabase secrets set BROWSERLESS_TOKEN=your_token`

## Optional — enhance but not required for core functionality

```
VITE_APP_VERSION=33
```
Displayed in Settings panel footer. Defaults to "dev" if not set.

## Notes

- All `VITE_` prefixed variables are bundled into the client JavaScript.
  Do not put secrets in `VITE_` variables.
- Supabase service role key is never used in this application.
  All database access uses the anon key + RLS policies.
- For local development: `cp .env.example .env.local`
  then replace placeholder values with your Supabase project credentials.
